text: Prunus schlechteri, aimangelo, is a species of Prunus native to New Guinea and the Solomon Islands. It is a tree reaching 35m. Native peoples chew a pulp of its bark to alleviate the pain of toothaches or apply it externally to relieve aching muscles.https://plants.jstor.org/stable/10.5555/al.ap.specimen.k000737408 ==References== schlechteri Category:Flora of Papuasia Category:Plants described in 1913 Category:Medicinal plants
